reviews:
*UPDATE: had these for over a year now and they've held up nicely after multiple washes and wears, there's very minimal pilling, and no holes or excess stretching.*

Pros: flattering, non see through, soft, comfortable, stretchy, sizing was accurate, phone pocket works well with my large samsung s9 plus, it's a good high waist length(reaches just above my belly button) great colour (however its a lilac purple colour not pink as advertised), its well made. And these are squat proof and dont fall down while you squat. Also the length is perfect it hits just below my ankles ( I'm 5,8")

Cons: They fall down a bit while walking so i have to hike them up sometimes. And it's a light colour so it shows the cellulite in my legs a bit. (Doesn't highlight it or anything but darker colours would hide cellulite better but, I wanted a light colour legging and this isn't a huge deal for me as cellulite is normal).

Overall I would highly reccommend these yoga pants to others.

If you found this review helpful please click the helpful button below :)

review_title: some sizing info for potential buyers
reviews:
I think how you like your leggings to fit will dictate the right size. i'm 5'9", 143lbs. per the size chart, I ordered a size large, but wish i had purchased the XL. they fit snug - not excruciatingly tight, but definitely snug - and i think the larger size would have been much more comfortable. if you like your leggings as fitted as tights, then go with the size chart. but if you prefer some give/flex, go for a size larger. (i like them so far, but have only washed them once so who knows? wish there was a cotton gusset at the crotch, though).

UPDATE with photo:
love these so much I bought another pair - this time in X-large. they're exactly how i like them to fit. snug enough that they're definitely leggings, but loose enough that I don't feel at all constricted. (and BTW - am about to buy another pair!)

UPDATE #2:
do NOT put them in the dryer. a lot of shrinkage, unless you air dry.

review_title: I am in love with these leggings
reviews:
I am in love with these leggings! They are so soft, and comfortable.

I was worried that I had ordered a size too big, but the XL was perfect, they stay put and don't ride down at all. I am 5'5", 190 pounds, I have thick thighs and a big butt, but the fabric doesn't stretch out or become see-through, honestly amazing quality for the price. The pockets are deep, and there is more than one pocket! They fit my Samsung Galaxy S8+ with room to spare.

I have only weight trained in these, and worn them out and about when I know I'll be doing a lot of walking, but have no complaints. I have washed them twice, and so far no peeling of any sort. Really excellent quality for the price you are paying.

I'll definitely be buying second pair.

***UPDATE***

I may be doubting my decision to go a size up, I find that after a few washes the leggings are becoming a little loose. They are not bouncing back to their original shape. This isn't too big of a deal as I can still use them for the gym, but if I keep my phone in the leggings they slip down a bit (especially if running). The other thing - these leggings will hold alllll your stink. So I would not recommend wearing them after your workout. I probably will only use these for training days, and yoga. Changing my 5 stars to 3.5/4 stars, as they are still a great value and are so comfy.

review_title: RIPPED IN THE BUM DURING SQUATS
reviews: I got these pants in black and dark blue first and washed them once before wearing them (with fabric softer and detergent) and they were amazing. Very soft, still amazingly fitted, and squat/gym proof. I decided to get a third pair because I really liked the burgundy colour and so I did. I didn't wash them with fabric softer this time just as the instructions advise, but unfortunately the most horrifying thing happened and they RIPPED in my bum area while I was doing the leg press/squatting at the gym. Thank goodness it was really early in the morning (not many people there) and I was able to run to the washroom and go home. Very disappointing! I think if I ever get these again I would just personally wash them one time with fabric softer (you don't need to do this every time) like I did with my first set just to give it that little extra stretchiness because that honestly worked so well for me with the first set of pants I got. Also kind of awful - but Amazon and this company haven't even gotten back to me about this and all I wanted was a replacement. Maybe they are just taking a while but over all right now I'm really disappointed.

reviews: I measure a product on the basis of functionality, fit and price. Highly recommend, I want to get more colours as well!!

review_title: ALONG FIT Hits It Out Of The Park With Their 'Yoga Pants' Alternative To Lululemon
reviews:
First off, I'm a tall woman, of 6' 3" stature, with a waist measurement of 33", my weight at 184 lbs (but I look slim with legs half as long as my body). The product size chart pegged me at XXL. I asked, to be sure with a question to ALONG FIT's representative. Let me say that originally I ordered a size XXL on advice from that representative. They were slightly off BUT they more than made up for it by rectifying the original problem by sending me an XL size.

Speed of delivery was great! Actually delivered earlier than what Amazon.ca quoted they would arrive by.

These XL yoga pants fit PERFECTLY!!!!!

For those who are tall like me with a 33 inch waist and roughly in the weight range of 175-190 lbs I highly recommend ordering the XL size yoga pants. The chart is slightly off - an XL will suffice for you tall ladies. They fit true to size if you naturally order an XL leggings or yoga pants.

The price is PURRFECT! As is the style and feel. Very velvet-like to the touch. Very VERY comfortable. Keeps your legs warm in fall (I assume winter maybe too) weather, but cooler during summer temps. There are smartphone pockets on the side of your thighs, and a small front pocket hidden in the front waist band for credit cards and/or keys.

I've already got compliments from other ladies, when used in conjunction with over-the-knee black slouch boots or knee-high leather heeled boots. The men seem to like them too. No complaints there!!! They enhance and amplify that "ohhh so sexy" look for ladies who want to feel comfortable yet wish to speak "I'm fashionable" by matching it will other fashion footwear.

They don't bind nor roll down from off the waist - they keep their grip on your tummy and even help reduce any pooch in the tummy region.

They wick off moisture really well. Plus they are thick enough not to show off your underwear through the fabric. They do good here. Panty lines "might" barely show (depending how thick the band is), but not the underwear patterns or what colour you're wearing.

Kudos to ALONG FIT for making such an amazing pair of yoga pants. Now that I know they carry my size I'll be ordering more of these in the future - if they keep their existing price.

My advice - run don't walk to ALONG FIT instead of purchasing more expensive yoga pants. Their quality is exactly similar to many other high quality yoga pants in the marketplace - including Lululemon.
